    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Hey, hey.",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 13.74
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "listeningistening to me.",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 31.84
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Okay, I\u2019m listening.",
      "at_sec": 32.57
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "I something.",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 37.71
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Could you please clarify what you're saying?",
      "at_sec": 38.33
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "text": "Tell me a long story.",
      "mode": "assistant",
      "at_sec": 42.94
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "The old lighthouse keeper, Silas, had seen a lot of storms in his seventy years, but nothing like the one brewing now.",
      "at_sec": 43.99
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "It wasn't just the wind, howling like a hungry wolf, or the rain, lashing against the thick glass of the lantern room.",
      "at_sec": 44.52
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "It was the feeling, a deep unease that settled in his bones like the damp chill of the sea.",
      "at_sec": 44.91
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Silas had inherited the lighthouse from his father, who had inherited it from his grandfather \u2013 a legacy of guiding ships safely through the treacherous Devil\u2019s Reef.",
      "at_sec": 45.52
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "He\u2019d always found comfort in the rhythmic sweep of the light, a promise of hope against the darkness.",
      "at_sec": 45.93
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "But tonight, the light felt fragile, a tiny spark against an encroaching doom.",
      "at_sec": 46.24
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "He remembered his grandfather\u2019s tales, whispered stories of a creature said to dwell in the deepest trenches of the ocean, a being of immense power and ancient sorrow known only as the Murk.",
      "at_sec": 46.98
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Sailors would speak of it in hushed tones, blaming sudden squalls and inexplicable disappearances on its wrath.",
      "at_sec": 47.38
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Silas had dismissed them as folklore, the fanciful exaggerations of men at sea, until tonight.",
      "at_sec": 47.73
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Earlier that day, a small fishing boat had been caught in the outer edges of the storm.",
      "at_sec": 48.1
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Silas had watched, helpless, as it battled the waves.",
      "at_sec": 48.32
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Just as he was about to radio for help, the boat vanished.",
      "at_sec": 48.59
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Not sunk, not capsized, simply\u2026gone.",
      "at_sec": 48.79
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "He'd scanned the turbulent water until his eyes ached, but there was nothing to be seen.",
      "at_sec": 49.18
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "It was as if the sea had swallowed it whole.",
      "at_sec": 49.38
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Then, the water began to glow.",
      "at_sec": 49.55
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "A faint, ethereal luminescence emanated from the depths, growing brighter with each passing moment.",
      "at_sec": 49.89
    }
  ],
